courses.learning_outcomes:
Upon completion of the Course, EP Trainees will be able to:
1. Demonstrate awareness and critical thinking of their assumptions, attitudes, beliefs, and values in relation to their multicultural competencies as an educational psychologist;
2. Apply various multicultural concepts, theories and models to their personal life as well as professional experiences;
3. Demonstrate knowledge and ability to develop and implement culture-sensitive interventions to meet the needs of diverse populations.

(Individual course teachers may update the learning outcome as and whenever necessary.)
